{"lemma":"عَلَقاتٌ","slug":"عَلَقاتٌ","root":"ع.ل.ق","root_slug":"ع-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَلَقَة","root":"علق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30277","n30283","n30284","n30285"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"leech","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"portion of blood","tags":["singulative"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"portion of thick or clotted blood","tags":["singulative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew עֲלוּקָה ('aluká); Arabic علق (various verbs); Classical Syriac ܥܰܠܘܽܩܳܐ (ˁallūq, ˁallūqā) or Jewish Babylonian Aramaic עַלקָא (ˁelləqā, ˁellaqṯā), or Akkadian [script needed] (ilku, ilḳitu)?"},"ipa":["/ʕa.la.qa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30277","headword_ar":"علّقهُ","root":"Elq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoliyqN","text_ar":"تَعْلِيقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElqhu","text_ar":"اعلقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * O, * Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEl~qhu","text_ar":"تعلّقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) signify the same. (S, O, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"علّق الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAl$~aYo'i","text_ar":"بِالشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"suspended, the thing to the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"مِنَ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made the thing to cling, catch, cleave, adhere, hold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick fast, to the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi","text_ar":"بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElqhu","text_ar":"اعلقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [For ex.,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqotu ri$aAy^iY biri$aAy^ika","text_ar":"عَلَّقْتُ رِشَايِى بِرِشَايِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have suspended my well-rope to thy well-rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ri$aA='ahu biri$aA='i Albiy^ori","text_ar":"رِشَا=ءَهُ بِرِشَا=ءِ البِيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaqa","text_ar":"اَعْلَقَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He suspended his well-rope to the rope of the well"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) [See also an ex. of the latter verb in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAfiDN","text_ar":"رَافِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~qhu EalaY Alwatidi","text_ar":"علّقهُ عَلَى الوَتِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung it on the peg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q Al$~aYo'a xalofahu","text_ar":"علّق الشَّىْءَ خَلْفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung the thing behind him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as, for instance, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haqiybap","text_ar":"حَقِيبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., behind the camel's saddle. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaA*apF","text_ar":"مَعَاذَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEl~q","text_ar":"تعلّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqa","text_ar":"عَلَّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon himself an amulet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlgarobi baEiyrayoni","text_ar":"بِالغَرْبِ بَعِيرَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElq","text_ar":"اعلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He coupled two camels to the end of the well-rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the other end of which was attached the large bucket"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IF, K.) [And in like manner they say in the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q Alxayola fiY AlEarabapi","text_ar":"علّق الخَيْلَ فِى العَرَبَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He harnessed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attached, the horses to the carriage."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aZofaArahu fiY Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"اَظْفَارَهُ فِى الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElq","text_ar":"اعلق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his nails to cling, catch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleave, to the thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And [in like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q yadahu","text_ar":"علّق يَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElqhA","text_ar":"اعلقها","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his hands to cling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.], followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"before the object: both signify the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"علّق الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q EalayohaA","text_ar":"علّق عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q ElyhA","text_ar":"علّق عليها"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmixolaApa","text_ar":"المِخْلَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with modern usage, i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hung upon the beast the nose-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"containing barley, or the like; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he supplied the beast with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealiyq","text_ar":"عَلِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barley,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, that is hung upon the beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [And hence, as is indicated in the T and TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q","text_ar":"علّق"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, by a metaphor, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He supplied with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealiyq","text_ar":"عَلِيق"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wine."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q raAHilatahu","text_ar":"علّق رَاحِلَتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He loosed the halter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leading-rope, from the muzzle of his riding-camel and threw it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hung it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon her shoulders, to give her ease."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [The primary significations are those mentioned in the second sentence of this paragraph: and hence several other significations here following. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~qhu bika*aA","text_ar":"علّقهُ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY ka*aA","text_ar":"عَلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it to depend upon such a thing, as a condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqotu Eitoqa EabodiY bimawotiY","text_ar":"عَلَّقْتُ عِتْقَ عَبْدِى بِمَوْتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made the freedom of my slave to depend upon my death"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dbr","text_ar":"دبر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino A^anoTiqo A^uTal~aqo waA_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ اَنْطِقْ اُطَلَّقْ وَاـِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asokuto A^uEal~aqo","text_ar":"اَسْكُتْ اُعَلَّقْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the story of Umm-Zara, means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If I speak, I am divorced; and if I be silent, I am left in suspense,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,] he leaves me like that which is suspended, (O, TA,) neither retained nor divorced. (TA.) [And similar to this is the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoliyqu A^afoEaAli Alquluwbi","text_ar":"تَعْلِيقُ اَفْعَالِ القُلُوبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The suspending of the verbs significant of operations of the mind from government, as to the letter but not as to the meaning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEal~aqN","text_ar":"مُعَلَّقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q AlbinaA='a","text_ar":"علّق البِنَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made the building,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"structure, pensile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported above the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above a stage"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"floor, by pillars"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"otherwise."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence,] the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqabuwA","text_ar":"نَقَبُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaAy^iTa waEal~aquwhu","text_ar":"الحَايِطَ وَعَلَّقُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They dug beneath the wall"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made a hole through it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and left it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEal~aqFA","text_ar":"مُعَلَّقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pensile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supported above the ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"being partially hollowed beneath]. (Mgh.) ―         -b6-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q fiY HaA$iyapi kitaAbK","text_ar":"علّق فِى حَاشِيَةِ كِتَابٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He appended a note in the margin of a book"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"El~q baAbFA","text_ar":"علّق بَابًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He set up, and fixed, a door,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY daArihi","text_ar":"عَلَى دَارِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to, his house"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b8-  And (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made fast, a door, with a kind of latch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sliding bolt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azolajahu","text_ar":"اَزْلَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arotajahu","text_ar":"اَرْتَجَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AElqhu","text_ar":"اعلقهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEolaAqN","text_ar":"مِعْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iqahaA","text_ar":"عُلِّقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iqa bihaA","text_ar":"عُلِّقَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which the pronoun denoting the object relates to a woman: see 1, former half. ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqa fulaAnN dama fulaAnK","text_ar":"عَلَّقَ فُلَانٌ دَمَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one attached to himself responsibility for the blood of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said when the former is the slayer of the latter. (TA. [Thus I find the phrase there written: but perhaps the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~iqa","text_ar":"عُلِّقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqahu","text_ar":"عَلَّقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He joined him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overtook him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b12-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He learned it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took it"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from another]. (TA.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~iquwA ramaqahu bi$aYo'K","text_ar":"عَلِّقُوا رَمَقَهُ بِشَىْءٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give ye to him something that shall stay,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrest, what remains in him of life."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~aqotu","text_ar":"عَلَّقْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa fulaAnK EaliyqapF","text_ar":"مَعَ فُلَانٍ عَلِيقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEa Alqawomi","text_ar":"مَعَ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sent with such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a camel for the purpose of bringing corn for me upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliyqapN","text_ar":"عَلِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"},{"kind":"quote","text":"AiroDa mina Almarokabi biAlt~aEoliyqi"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2134},{"kind":"text","text":"is a prov., said to a man who is thereby enjoined to be content with a part of that which he wants, instead of the whole thereof; like him who rides the camel termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealiyqap","text_ar":"عَلِيقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"one time after another time: [so that it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Be thou content, instead of the riding"},{"kind":"text","text":"constantly, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instead of the beast that is ridden"},{"kind":"text","text":"only,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the sending a camel to bring corn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"upon which thou mayest ride occasionally:] (TA:) or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou content, instead of"},{"kind":"text","text":"thy"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"riding, with the hanging"},{"kind":"text","text":"of thy goods upon the beast: or the meaning may be,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou content, in respect of the beast that is ridden, with the hanging"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thy goods] upon him in thy turn. (Meyd.) ―         -b15-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eal~iqo linaAqatiki","text_ar":"عَلِّقْ لِنَاقَتِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Go thou from thy she-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aimo$i EanohaA","text_ar":"اِمْشِ عَنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30283","headword_ar":"عَلْقَةٌ","root":"Elq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ja*obap","text_ar":"جَذْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fray,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being a kind of strain,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is occasioned in a garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and other"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"similar"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing when one passes by a thorn or a tree."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaloqN","text_ar":"عَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30284","headword_ar":"عُلْقَةٌ","root":"Elq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqapN","text_ar":"عَلَاقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", former half, in two places. ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quantity that suffices the cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what they obtain from the trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plants"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaqN","text_ar":"عَلَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqN","text_ar":"عَلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqapN","text_ar":"عَلَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sufficiency of the means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever it be;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqN","text_ar":"عَلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqapN","text_ar":"عَلَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or it signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food sufficient to retain life;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutaEal~aqN","text_ar":"مُتَعَلَّقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqN","text_ar":"عَلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajiyEN","text_ar":"رَجِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjE","text_ar":"رجع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and, (O, K, TA,) accord. to AHn, (O, TA,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trees that remain in the winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of which the camels are fed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the camels suffice themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until they attain to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rabiyE","text_ar":"رَبِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spring-herbage"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, K, TA: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurowapN","text_ar":"عُرْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and it is also expl. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"herbage that does not stay:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food that suffices until the time of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"morning-meal called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gadaA='","text_ar":"غَدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqN","text_ar":"عَلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) and accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beast for riding, such as suffices one, though it be not free from deficiency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defect:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuloqapN","text_ar":"عُلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EulaqN","text_ar":"عُلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liY fiY h`*aA AlmaAli","text_ar":"لِى فِى هٰذَا المَالِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuloqapN","text_ar":"عُلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiloqN","text_ar":"عِلْقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuluwqN","text_ar":"عُلُوقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqapN","text_ar":"عَلَاقَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mataEal~aqN","text_ar":"مَتَعَلَّقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", all meaning the same, (K, TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is for me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have, in this property,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sufficiency of the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yaA^okulu fulaAnN A_il~aA EuloqapF","text_ar":"مَا يَاْكُلُ فُلَانٌ اـِلَّا عُلْقَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one eats not save a bare sufficiency of the means of subsistence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA *uqotu EalaAqFA","text_ar":"مَا ذُقْتُ عَلَاقًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not tasted a sufficiency of the means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"food sufficient to retain life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA fiY","text_ar":"مَا فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA lamaAqN","text_ar":"وَلَا لَمَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi EalaAqN","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ عَلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is not in the land a sufficiency of the means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pasturage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA bihaA mino EalaAqK","text_ar":"مَا بِهَا مِنْ عَلَاقٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"there is not in it pasturage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yatoruki AlHaAlibu biAln~aAqapi","text_ar":"لَمْ يَتْرُكِ الحَالِبُ بِالنَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAqFA","text_ar":"عَلَاقًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The milker did not leave in the she-camel's udder anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaluwqN","text_ar":"عَلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yaboqa liY Einodahu EuloqapN","text_ar":"لَمْ يَبْقَ لِى عِنْدَهُ عُلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There remained not with him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, * K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlkalaAmu lanaA fiyhi EuloqapN","text_ar":"هٰذَا الكَلَامُ لَنَا فِيهِ عُلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In this speech is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sufficiency"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for us"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einodahumo","text_ar":"عِنْدَهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuloqapN mino mataAEihimo","text_ar":"عُلْقَةٌ مِنْ مَتَاعِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With them is"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"somewhat remaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30285","headword_ar":"عِلْقَةٌ","root":"Elq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first garment that is made for a boy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a shirt without sleeves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment in which is cut an opening for the head to be put through it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that nearly one half of it falls down before the wearer and the corresponding portion behind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having its two sides sewn"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is worn by a girl;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sudorap","text_ar":"صُدْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she uses it for service and work;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and it extends to the place of the waist-band:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_itobN","text_ar":"اـِتْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment held in high estimation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiloqN","text_ar":"عِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[mentioned before];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"one says of him who has not upon him costly garments,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA Ealayohi EiloqapN","text_ar":"مَا عَلَيْهِ عِلْقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not upon him costly attire"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shield."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, O, TA. [This last meaning is also assigned to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiloqN","text_ar":"عِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as mentioned before.])       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain tree, used for tanning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibil","text_ar":"اـِبِل"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa bihaA EliqapN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ بِهَا علِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase mentioned by Ibn-'Abbád, (O, TA,) as meaning [app.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASrp","text_ar":"اصرة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [This word, in the TA, is blurred: and in the O, the place that it occupied has perished: I think that it is most probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSir~apN","text_ar":"اَصِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraArN","text_ar":"صِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore that the phrase means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Camels not having upon them strings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of rag, bound upon their udders"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teats, to prevent their young ones from sucking:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sar~a biAln~aAqapi","text_ar":"صَرَّ بِالنَّاقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sar~a Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"صَرَّ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in like manner, I suppose, one may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa bihaA A^aSir~apN","text_ar":"لَيْسَ بِهَا اَصِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence, perhaps, it may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~aAqapi EaluwqN","text_ar":"بِالنَّاقَةِ عَلُوقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A4-  [For the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaA^oSala A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"اِسْتَاْصَلَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiloqaAtahuimo","text_ar":"عِلْقَاتَهُِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see the next paragraph but one.]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]}]}}